What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Standalone Personal Emergency Response Systems Market?

Standalone Personal Emergency Response Systems Market Analysis

Standalone personal emergency response systems (PERS) are evolving with advancements in wearables, integrating GPS and LTE technology for real-time tracking and faster response. These systems enhance user safety and accessibility, driving market growth. Innovations such as fall detection and voice-activated features further boost adoption, with the market expanding as demand for personalized safety solutions rises.

Standalone Personal Emergency Response Systems Market Size

The global standalone personal emergency response systems market size was valued at USD 5.86 billion in 2023 and is projected to reach USD 9.48 billion by 2031, with a CAGR of 6.2% during the forecast period of 2024 to 2031. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include in-depth expert analysis, geographically represented company-wise production and capacity, network layouts of distributors and partners, detailed and updated price trend analysis and deficit analysis of supply chain and demand.

Standalone Personal Emergency Response Systems Market Trends

“Integration with Smart Home Technologies”

The integration of standalone personal emergency response systems (PERS) with smart home technologies is a significant trend driving market growth. These systems now seamlessly connect with smart devices such as home assistants, smart thermostats, and security cameras, enhancing their functionality and appeal. For instance, companies such as Life Alert have developed systems that can automatically alert emergency services when paired with smart home devices, ensuring quicker response times and improved user safety. This integration not only boosts the efficiency of emergency responses but also provides added convenience and peace of mind for users, contributing to the increasing adoption and market expansion of standalone PERS.

